One of my favorite brekfast burritos. The pancakes are great too. Really friendly staff.
Friendly. Good food.
Great breakfast, whether you just want a bowl of oatmeal or super hungry, they have something for you on the menu.
OMG. We ate here twice during out San Diego visit. Both lunch and breakfast were delicious. Servings are large. Limited seating. Service was excellent.
Great Pork Tenderloins (like from the mid west)! Finding a place to park can be a problem. Several One Way streets, so be aware. WORTH a trip if you like Tenderloins.

It was good. I'd been jonesing for a hot dog for a couple of days and this hit the spot. They didn't put cheese on it so... I don't know how they sleep at night. Maybe a white noise machine or something.

My daughter and I went here for breakfast when visiting the city. The food was excellent and the service was fast and very friendly, all for a very nice price. If you just want to stop in quick and get a good breakfast without getting fancy, then come here.

Love the vibe and old school diner style. Friendly staff, quick service and the food was really good. I got a strawberry chicken salad with candied walnuts. Not a hard dish by any means, but proportions were excellent, and presentation was perfect. Overall, I'd definitely recommend.
A small place with great breakfast

Fast and friendly service. Get there early! It's a small place that gets crowded quick. I've been there several times and everything was delicious. Get the "Bases Loaded" breakfast burrito and an OJ and you'll be good to go until dinner. …
Excellent!! Clean, well priced, delicious!
Great service!
Seriously the best diner in San Diego!
Amazing place to grab breakfast! Fresh food,  sparkling clean inside, super friendly staff. The pancakes were amazing.  I had a burrito.  Yum.
